cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SD 

This paper proposes a new neural network architecture for speech recognition, which involves modeling long-term temporal dependencies using deep feed-forward layers with residual and time-delayed connections. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CL (Computation and Language) for speech recognition, cs.LG (Machine Learning) for the development of a new neural network architecture, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) for the use of neural networks, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) for the application of the architecture to speech recognition, and cs.SD (Sound) for the focus on speech recognition.
